Let’s load an image of the area of interest. We also create a new raster called r_aoi, a binary raster that can mask out certain areas. In this example, every pixel of the image is of interest so r_aoi is a raster of ones.

tif <- system.file("tif/L7_ETMs.tif", package = "stars")
s <- stack(tif)

plotRGB(s)

# We now create r_aoi 
r_aoi <- subset(s, 1)
names(r_aoi) <- c('aoi')
r_aoi[] <- 1

Generating a sample to compute the \(I_B\) for

We now generate 150 random samples from the area of interest and compute their respective \(I_B\).

n_sample <- 500 # size of each sample

# We generate the random samples
ref_sample <- get_random_population(aoi=r_aoi, values=s, n_pop=n_sample) %>%
                  sf::st_as_sf() %>% 
                  dplyr::select(-one_of('aoi')) %>% 
                  dplyr::mutate(id=1:dplyr::n()) %>% 
                  tidyr::drop_na()

plot(raster::subset(s, 1))
points(as(ref_sample, "Spatial"), add=T)
## Warning in plot.xy(xy.coords(x, y), type = type, ...): "add" is not a graphical
## parameter

Generating random samples

We now generate 150 random samples from the area of interest and compute their respective \(I_B\).

n <- 10 # number of samples to draw 
n_sample <- 500 # size of each sample



# We generate the random samples
my_samples <- future_lapply(1:n,
                            function(x, aoi, values, n_pop) get_random_population(aoi=aoi, values=values, n_pop=n_pop),
                            aoi=r_aoi, values=s, n_pop=n_sample)

# And write them to disk
my_samples <- future_lapply(1:n,
              function(x, my_samples) 
                my_samples[[x]] %>%
                  sf::st_as_sf() %>% 
                  dplyr::select(-one_of('aoi')) %>% 
                  dplyr::mutate(id=1:dplyr::n()) %>% 
                  tidyr::drop_na() %>% 
                sf::st_write(glue::glue(file.path(getwd(), 'data', paste0(n_sample,'_random_sample_{stringr::str_pad(x, 3, pad = "0")}.shp'))),
                             delete_layer=TRUE, delete_dsn=TRUE),
              my_samples=my_samples)
